        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2021-11-25 13:30:03.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nCouple of observations:\n1. The Service Property/Service Instance drop down box seems to remain greyed out even when there is valid options to select from\n2. Does the selection of a Service Input from a VF instance make sense, should it not be only possible to select an input from self. The generated tosca does not connect the input to be retrieved to an instance\n3. For get_property for a property on the service itself (as opposed to a VF instance) the first element in the generated tosca is the name of the service - should this not be 'SELF'\n4. - select a VF instance\n   - open the 'Directives and Node Filter' tab\n   - then add a new VF instance to the composition\n   - then add a node filter to the already selected VF\n   - the newly added VF does not appear in the Source drop down\nSome of these are possibly faults in the existing implementation and can be taken in separate bugs if that is the case",
        "patchset_number": 1
      },
      {
        "id": "1a4384dea2bcf890cc3f7882914cd751252c4da7",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 5629,
          "name": "Anderson Ribeiro",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "anderson.ribeiro@est.tech",
          "username": "aribeiro"
        },
        "author_role": "OWNER",
        "timestamp": "2021-11-25 15:56:16.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\n> Patch Set 1:\n> \n> Couple of observations:\n> 1. The Service Property/Service Instance drop down box seems to remain greyed out even when there is valid options to select from\n> 2. Does the selection of a Service Input from a VF instance make sense, should it not be only possible to select an input from self. The generated tosca does not connect the input to be retrieved to an instance\n> 3. For get_property for a property on the service itself (as opposed to a VF instance) the first element in the generated tosca is the name of the service - should this not be 'SELF'\n> 4. - select a VF instance\n>    - open the 'Directives and Node Filter' tab\n>    - then add a new VF instance to the composition\n>    - then add a node filter to the already selected VF\n>    - the newly added VF does not appear in the Source drop down\n> Some of these are possibly faults in the existing implementation and can be taken in separate bugs if that is the case\n\nHi Michael, I will create a bug ticket to address the issues reported on the items 1, 3 and 4. Those are present on the existing implementation.",
        "patchset_number": 1
      },
